      • getIndicator

        public final String getIndicator()
        Description copied from interface: PrologTerm
        Gets the term indicator represented by one string with the format functor/arity. More formally the indicator string is formed by the concatenation of PrologTerm.getFunctor() and PrologTerm.getArity() separated by slash.
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        term indicator
